[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Exploring Scala array options**\n\nI’m thinking about using public Scala compiler toolboxes for generating classes, but it seems not directly applicable with Native. I can use scala.util.matching.Regex, which could potentially help. I wonder if 161 standard object instances would be enough, but it feels a bit excessive. How about arrays of different primitive and object arrays? Each array class being distinct could open up interesting possibilities, especially with reflection. Arrays inherit public Object methods and there's something in Class.getMethod returning Object.toString. I’ll keep exploring this!", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0ab739bc3b3726c90169f534c662088192b74d83562d1a2fe2\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp9TTdbyNeBsZz5VVHuAS8i_OcFsClBkU4EhiLvM6EDXNR2ZE57oC3XKc-P96gn-RiaY0UcAXxibMt2t2S6jVA2jqUdI0nL351eJphLRTvmFR0n_dMcDEbfntFAFAxImzsjQ8iyb-e1cRh_ZS6em-u3G7L4kB_p9SdlWFBxovBwvF9oMe0BygmyqNBzbQF7NqbEcwNpvJn7zNyZ2IwtcNVIEoVUkQqoDgs6zPdv1c3WXo-pVvYchX7tdqhk071LC4ODCvJ9fNLtsZG5y_wAKrQuFi1dKIsn5EnVpUf_esZQGm--y5lN0cRXj_5jHJj2_521PtPMemflNhE4wNGPj3vOGthlpqR5IzqBAs2oa7vTZLU6jC28YZDSznEAviV9vLeQpD1qDxuB9hJLP9D6kYnSqiJVg7mZtvIR6GnIeEqjJJb6rLE9rR_276CC_vV0ZACOgR3YcbGBEnva4SMhDwFsXKCgDC-ayGSD1cDBRcWVpighrhZM-CnYgxzUbfC5RbsxPljlM3LJ9C219Qo3ka9TP5wGil_6XiJcuYBNm5m5j-i2yx0oMINDW_R0sCq7XSBXuE51LCzpzFMVrE3xE7Rahjgv9DD_hNThi-wIDWv8pP3r7raOd-aD1r_b7dXOLeFj1sCrCvODniHaINNTYAIB6RZyHLzfrJIdX7AQjtRy1HmEN1WGpArs6KZrLkp8WUYQ8OCeJchr8sy7pa0sP5lHaaGEZbY6jh5IrF7aH7YknJ5l4dZePjBLBvVYltSUM8CDQPHWtVFUttABcJleV5pKFTw5kqQjw6UXwk5dtdWT7tB3q4rpqmOPXo7kxk6o-1wNYCcOMiOPDuKTLgR1GzXlGEHDpCZb5opi3AkB9UvRP6_2Gdz0RdA1fIUjIoiJC2AIgfY54ex9BF9P2y_4GNZmDCWZSdBse9CcVGRormaolz-qJ04Fdd_EcW1papuu6w2BHj_ojtaaG396X7yx019EADtuypcp3uBi5Mi-klGM6MpDycRWL-efuYgvdr2JGJJImzy-VFlx-nDQasTjsVcPLMajKc_J74-XDaAiLKHxi_LPbhxKw_1fesahGJmfuupaGZ1O3Tlnpdckl-vH8Bmg3CditAshRDM74dYXxUlHncJS